The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Buchanan in city today
                                                   Buchanan in city today
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: John Buchanan, coach of the Calcutta team in the Indian Premier League (IPL), will arrive in the city on Monday.         
	The former Australia coach, who will be staying for a couple of days, will meet Calcutta captain Sourav Ganguly and team owner Shah Rukh Khan during the visit.         
	The name of the side, team jersey and theme song will be announced on Tuesday in the presence of Shah Rukh.         
	However, the CAB is yet to sort out the contentious ticket distribution issue for the ensuing matches.                                                                                                                       
